Text.Value: Remember the zaith'isk? These gith can't be trusted. Follow my lead - I'll choose the right path.
Attack.
This is what we have all been training for.
You really have no idea what it is, do you?
It was a vision of the future. Luckily, our queen is here to guide us. She will lead us to victory.
On second thoughts, I don't need anything of yours.
We took an interest in you when you became involved with this 'Absolute' cult. A pestilence of infected slaves - the first symptom of the Grand Design in action.
Indeed? And what does it protect you from?
The ghaik are about to execute their Grand Design and you seek to bargain. P'hak'va.
You have accomplished much since. I am pleased to finally meet you.
Your illustrious adventure ends here. Hta'zith!
Did your crèche teach you nothing? That knowledge belongs to Queen Vlaakith alone. It is not for us to know nor question.
The tadpole in my head.
Never.
No...
No...
Imagine that everywhere. Wants, needs, choice - all would cease to be.
The Grand Design is what all ghaik seek. The restoration of the Illithid Empire, which spanned the entirety of the multiverse.
Give me a treasure from the Githyanki Empire's coffers. One of immense power.
Hand over an artefact of immense power for nothing in return? You do insult me.
What do I get in return if I give it to you?

EditorData.logicalname: What do I get in return?

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* CINE_ProduceInventory for PLYR. For Inquisitor will need custom SCENE anim, can probably create one out of CINE_ReceiveItem & CINE_StartledTakeXXX. <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
The player reaches to produce the artefact. 
The inquisitor reaches to take it but is interrupted.

Text.Value: Fool. You were a mistake.
But I will humour your greed for a moment. What would you ask of an Inquisitor?
What is the Grand Design?
Don't give it to him.
Don't give it to him.
What makes you think we are not? We are talking about the Grand Design - the restoration of the Illithid Empire. There is nothing of greater importance.

EditorData.NodeContext: as if talking about something super obvious that you're an idiot not to have heard of

Text.Value: Ch'r'ai. Vlaakith's justice in flesh.
Kith'rak Voss' made a mistake when he let you go.
If you hear that voice at all, then you are infected.
Hand it over.
It must not have been easy to escape.
Give me the weapon. Now.
How will this weapon stop the mind flayers?
But know that you will have been instrumental in stopping the Grand Design.
I know a lot of ways to kill - but not the gith way. Teach me.
I know the gith as formidable warriors - teach me your ways of war.
Githyanki hunting parties are feared across the planes - teach me your ways.
You githyanki are disciplined warriors - I wish to learn your ways.
Here. Let me put your lights out. Hta'zith!
You saw the thralls gathered on the ghaik ship.
Perhaps you should leave the thinking to me, vin'iisk. Hand over the weapon.
Perhaps you should leave the thinking to me, istik. Hand over the weapon.
I can give it to you, but I don't think you'll like it.
Our fate is forged. Mother Gith, guide us!
The zaith'isk... Tsk - tsk - tsk'va! I hate that you speak the truth.

EditorData.NodeContext: tsk tsk tsk-VA! Basically saying, SHIT SHIT SHIT!

Text.Value: Never before could they pause ceremorphosis. Never before could they let the infection spread undetected.
And it is my people who need protecting from you. Hta'zith!
Everything rendered unto the ghaik.
Produce the artefact.
Is the ghaik incursion not more important?
I thought the Grand Design was a ghaik philosophy, not an actual plan.
Well you know what they say about fears. The best thing you can do is face them.
Is that so? Well, then - humour me. What would you ask of an Inquisitor?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: He's only playing along for his own entertainment. He doesn't believe we have anything to offer him.

Text.Value: However, you will readily witness our silver swords cleave putrid ghaik flesh if you do but one thing -
But you are lucky - that weapon you carry is the solution. I have heard it from Queen Vlaakith herself.
My ardents spoke of one of our kin that escaped a crashing ghaik slave-vessel.
Interesting. My ardents reported that an istik survived the crashed ghaik slave-vessel.
We are keeping the artefact.
I know my path. Refuse him the artefact, and it will run with your blood.
The weapon. Now.
I could use an ally against the illithids. As could you.
The voice of the Absolute.
No matter. Death will cure you of that problem.
The ch'r'ai speaks. You must obey.
Do it. Do not disobey the Inquisitor.
I heard there is so much goblin blood on your hands that it soaks their children's nightmares.
You have accomplished much, child. I am pleased to finally meet you.
Here's how deals like this work: I have something you need. I can bargain all I like.
A promotion in the eyes of our Queen. I want my silver sword.
Once the Grand Design comes into effect and the Illithid Empire is restored, all life will be over as you know it.
I do not know what base, naive entities you have made deals with before - nor do I care.
*The artefact stirs in your pocket. Right within your grasp, and desperate not to be relinquished.*
I'm not inclined to give away valuable things for free. You want it, make an offer.
I have the weapon - I would say that puts me in a strong position to bargain with you.
That is a secret known only to Queen Vlaakith. Its significance is beyond both of our stations.
You test our Queen's patience. Surrender the artefact, or die by my hand.
Do not try me. Hand over the artefact, or die by my hand.

EditorData.NodeContext: Threatening and confident. She means what she says.

Text.Value: But the weapon is the solution. I have heard it directly from Queen Vlaakith herself.
The weapon. Give it to me.
This weapon - what does it do?
I heard enough druids died by your hand to make the deity Silvanus himself weep.
It is how we will stop the mind flayers before they destroy us all.
I bet your empire has gathered countless valuable spellbooks in its time - let me read them.
How do you know so much about me?
My mind is silver, and my body steel. Vlaakith expects no less of me.
I suspect you plucked something precious from the ghaik ship. Something our queen has been looking for.
To business. I suspect you plucked something precious from the ghaik ship. Something that belongs to us.
You stand before an Inquisitor of Vlaakith and ask for... reading material?
Some of your species say knowledge is power. They are wrong. Knowledge is everything.
Place the weapon in the planecaster. Fulfil my Queen's most holy edict.
Place the weapon in the planecaster. Fulfil our Queen's most holy edict.
You can't trust him, Lae'zel. Follow my lead. I will choose the right path.
Only this? Gladly. Once you hand me the artefact.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: You had the chance to negotiate for something more and blew it on something he was going to give you anyway.

Text.Value: You will have it, ra'stil. Our silver will light this world's sky in righteous crusade.
If you desire to see the might of my people, you will not be disappointed.
You would lay claim to our hard-won treasures? You seek power but do not seek to strive for it?
Our swords are ready to cleave ghaik flesh in their legions. With or without your interference.
Tsk - tsk - tsk'va! I hate that you speak the truth.

EditorData.NodeContext: tsk tsk tsk-VA! Basically saying, SHIT SHIT SHIT!

Text.Value: All kinds of bad things. It's my lucky charm.
My ardents spoke of one of our kin that escaped a crashing ghaik slave-vessel.
I won't let you take it.
I have seen your behaviour before. The squirming, the avoidance. You are infected.
Coin, typically - but anything of immense value will do.
Gish war-arts far eclipse the reckoning of istik minds.
But you were not wrong to observe that you need protection.
Shouldn't you be more concerned with the mind flayer invasion?
How will this weapon actually stop the ghaik?
You can't trust him, Lae'zel. Follow my lead. I will choose the right path.
I can't. It protects me.
You are infected? Grotesque.
What business is that of yours? Suffice to say, our queen wants it.
What business is that of yours? Suffice to say, my queen wants it.
Then your illustrious adventure ends here. Hta'zith!
So. The weapon. Please.
Make me your best offer. I accept gold.
A fool's request. Denied.
You know more than you're letting on.
Choose. Your path is mine to follow.
You hold the key to thwarting the ghaik Grand Design - and you ask me for coin? Petty trinkets?
You mean the Grand Design? The restoration of the Illithid Empire? Why, it is of the utmost importance.

EditorData.NodeContext: as if talking about something super obvious that you're an idiot not to have heard of

Text.Value: Produce the artefact.
You also killed Sarth Baretha. She was formidable.
As is your will, ch'r'ai.
Don't do it. The weapon is how I protect you.
Don't do it. The weapon is how I protect you.
The dark?
For centuries, their elder brains sought to bring back their dominion. Every plot they hatched, we stopped. But now, they are close to succeeding.

Synopsis: The inquisitor demands the Orpheus artefact. The player can ask questions or attempt to hand over the artefact, which leads to Vlaakith appearing through the planecaster. Vlaakith explains that there's a prisoner inside who needs to be killed for the safety of the gith and teleports the player into the Astral Prison. Alternatively the player can kill the inquisitor and prompt Vlaakith’s appearance themselves.
